Ankara is in the process of reconciliation with Damascus – a government it has harshly criticized over the last 12 years during the Syrian conflict. Many Syrians in rebel-held areas protested against the reconciliation and have expressed anger at the Turkish government. But Türkiye is also host to millions of Syrians who have fled the war. Some are anxious about what the rapprochement will mean for them. CGTN's Michal Bardavid reports.